standardHubID.name: standardHubID
standardHubID.description: A 48-bit unique identifier of the hub. Not to be confused with the 48-bit address of the MAC that may be used to obtain management access to the hub when in-band signaling is used. If a manufacturer builds a hub with an on-board MAP for communicating network management information, the manufacturer has the option to use the same address for both HubID and MAC address. This option is implemented by LANNET agents for LET-18 and LET- 36.

standardHubElapsedTimeSinceRest.name: standardHubElapsedTimeSinceRest
standardHubElapsedTimeSinceRest.description: The time in tens of milliseconds since the last time the hub was reset. This may have been caused by a RESET HUB action or by other means. This counter has a value of 0 when initialized. Setting the value of this attribute to zero is interpreted by LANNET agents as a RESET commnand. The required resolution is to the nearest 100 milliseconds.

standardHubExecuteSelfTest1.name: standardHubExecuteSelfTest1
standardHubExecuteSelfTest1.description: Perform self-test 1 on the hub. When this attribute is set to ON by the management console, the agent starts executing the hub test procedure. The attribute is reset to OFF at the end of the test procedure.

standardHubExecuteSelfTest2.name: standardHubExecuteSelfTest2
standardHubExecuteSelfTest2.description: Perform self test 2 on the hub. When this attribute is set to ON by the management console, he agent starts executing the hub test procedure. The attribute is reset to OFF at the end of the test procedure.

standardRelayID.name: standardRelayID
standardRelayID.description: The value used in addressing the relay. Value 1 is returned by LANNET SNMP agents for hubs LE-18 and LET-36

standardRelayNumberOfGroups.name: standardRelayNumberOfGroups
standardRelayNumberOfGroups.description: Number of groups related to relay. Range 1-255. In LANNET implementation it describes the number of manageable slots in the hub (not all slots should be ocuppied).

standardRelayTotalCollisions.name: standardRelayTotalCollisions
standardRelayTotalCollisions.description: Counter incremented every time the hub enters a condition caused by simultaneous transmission and detection of external activity on one or more of its ports.

standardRelayReset.name: standardRelayReset
standardRelayReset.description: Setting the value of this attribute to ON is interpreted as a relay reset command, which leads to the zeroing of all relay-related counters.

standardRelayCurTraffic.name: standardRelayCurTraffic
standardRelayCurTraffic.description: Record of traffic for the last second with a resolution of 100 msec. The traffic is expressed in percents of the maximum Ethernet traffic and each record contains 10 readings, in the range 1..20, expressed on a log(10) scale ( value = 10*log10(percent) ).

standardRelayTrafficTrsh.name: standardRelayTrafficTrsh
standardRelayTrafficTrsh.description: Traffic threshold value. When exceeded, a trap is send to the management console. Expressed in percents of the maximum Ethernet traffic, in the range 1..20, expressed on a log(10) scale.

standardRelayPeakTraffic.name: standardRelayPeakTraffic
standardRelayPeakTraffic.description: Maximal traffic value since last reset of hub or relay. Expressed in per- cents of the maximum Ethernet traffic, in the range 1..20, expressed on log(10) scale.

standardGroupID.name: standardGroupID
standardGroupID.description: Unique value identifying the group. In LANNET enclosures it equals the slot number of the related module (FRU).

standardGroupNumberOfPorts.name: standardGroupNumberOfPorts
standardGroupNumberOfPorts.description: Number of ports contained within the group. Valid range 1..255. Within each group the ports are assigned unique numbers range from 1 to standardGroupNumberOfPorts. They correspond to the number of ports in the module (FRU).

standardGroupAutoMan.name: standardGroupAutoMan
standardGroupAutoMan.description: This attribute reflects the status of the AUTO/MANual switch which defi- nes the working mode of LANNET sensors. In the Manual mode, no set operations may be performed on attributes related to the sensor. The sensor works accor- ding to configuration switches set in hardware and transmits all the configuration information to the agent. In the Auto, mode hardware switches are overridden by set commands.

standardGroupReset.name: standardGroupReset
standardGroupReset.description: Setting the value of this attribute to ON is interpreted as a software RESET command. Sensor software is reinitialized and according to the sensor specifications, partial or total reset of the module hardware may be performed.

standardPortType.name: standardPortType
standardPortType.description: Describes the port type from the point of view of its network functionali- ty. This characterization describes adherence to physical layer standards, while LANNET standard extensions are generally defined as private.

standardPortID.name: standardPortID
standardPortID.description: A value unique in each group. It is assumed that ports are partitioned into groups that also have IDs and are related to FRUs. This value can never exceed standardGroupNumberOfPorts. Range 0..255.

standardPortAdminStatus.name: standardPortAdminStatus
standardPortAdminStatus.description: A disabled port neither transmits nor receives. The port must be explici- tenly enabled to restore operation. standardPortAdminStatus takes precedence over AutoPartition.

standardPortAutoPartitionState.name: standardPortAutoPartitionState
standardPortAutoPartitionState.description: The AutoPart condition indicates that the port is currently partitioned by the auto-partition protection mechanism.

standardPortFramesReceivedOK.name: standardPortFramesReceivedOK
standardPortFramesReceivedOK.description: A representation of the total number of frames of legal length that have not been corrupted in transmission. These frames can be encoded and decoded by the commonly available MACs and provide a measure of the network bandwidth being used. The number does not include frames received with frame-too-long, FCS, alignment errors, frames lost due to internal MAC sublayer errors, runts or pygmys.

standardPortOctetsReceivedOK.name: standardPortOctetsReceivedOK
standardPortOctetsReceivedOK.description: Counter for the number of data and padding octets contained in the FramesReceivedOK counter.

standardPortCollisions.name: standardPortCollisions
standardPortCollisions.description: Counter incremented every time the hub enters a condition caused by simultaneous transmission and detection of external activity on this port.

standardPortFrameCheckSequence.name: standardPortFrameCheckSequence
standardPortFrameCheckSequence.description: Counter for the number of frames received on this port that are an integral number of octets in length and do not pass the FCS check.

standardPortSQETestNotDisabled.name: standardPortSQETestNotDisabled
standardPortSQETestNotDisabled.description: Settable attribute which allows activation of SQE test for LANNET integrated transceivers.

standardPortRunt.name: standardPortRunt
standardPortRunt.description: Counter for the number of collision fragments longer than a pygmy and shorter than a legal packet, detected on this port.

standardPortPygmy.name: standardPortPygmy
standardPortPygmy.description: Counter for the number of pygmy fragments received on this port. These fragments, less than 64 +/- 10 bits long, may indicate an external noise hit, a network problem.

standardPortOutOfRangeLenField.name: standardPortOutOfRangeLenField
standardPortOutOfRangeLenField.description: Counter for the number of packets received on this port whose length field indicate values greater than 2 ** 15 . Such packets gene- rally do not point to a network problem, but merely to the use of the IEEE 802.3 protocol instead of Ethernet, in which case the field has a different significance - protocol type. It may be used for counting the number of frames transmitted in each protocol.

standardPortFramesTooLong.name: standardPortFramesTooLong
standardPortFramesTooLong.description: Counter for the number of packets received on this port that are longer than 1518 octets, yet do not exceed the maximum range for the range field.

standardPortAlignmentErrors.name: standardPortAlignmentErrors
standardPortAlignmentErrors.description: Counter for the number of frames received though this port that are not an integral number of octets in length. Although these frames will not pass the FCS check, they are not counted as FCS errors, as the alignment errors have precedence in the standard error counting scheme.

standardPortAutoPartitionLog.name: standardPortAutoPartitionLog
standardPortAutoPartitionLog.description: Counter for the number of times the repeater has automatically partitio- ned this port.

standardPortOutOfSpecBitRate.name: standardPortOutOfSpecBitRate
standardPortOutOfSpecBitRate.description: Counter for the number of times a packet has been received by this port with the transmission frequency (data rate) detectable out of spec.

standardPortLastSourceAddress.name: standardPortLastSourceAddress
standardPortLastSourceAddress.description: Ethernet source address of the last readable frame received by this port.

standardPortSourceAdressChanges.name: standardPortSourceAdressChanges
standardPortSourceAdressChanges.description: Counter for the number of times the last source address has changed.

standardPortExecuteTest.name: standardPortExecuteTest
standardPortExecuteTest.description: Setting to the value of this attribute to ON (determines the port to enter) self-test mode.

standardPortTraffic.name: standardPortTraffic
standardPortTraffic.description: Counter for the number of bits received on this port in frames with legal length information.

standardPortPacketErrors.name: standardPortPacketErrors
standardPortPacketErrors.description: Counter for the number of frames with errors detected on the port by the LANNET agent hardware. This generic port error comprises too long packets, CRC and alignment errors.

standardPortUserStatus.name: standardPortUserStatus
standardPortUserStatus.description: Attribute defining the connection of a port to a single Ethernet source or to a multi-source (segment or star).

standardPortGroupID.name: standardPortGroupID
standardPortGroupID.description: ID of group which contains the port

mgrIPaddr.name: mgrIPaddr
mgrIPaddr.description: IP address of the network management console.

mgrTrapRepStat.name: mgrTrapRepStat
mgrTrapRepStat.description: ON indicates that SNMP agent should send SNMP traps (relay traffic ex- cluded) to the manager.

mgrContPerformanceRep.name: mgrContPerformanceRep
mgrContPerformanceRep.description: ON indicates that the SNMP agent should send relay traffic SNMP traps to the manager.

mgrMngmntState.name: mgrMngmntState
mgrMngmntState.description: Attribute to be set by manager in order to instruct the agent to enter into a management session with the console. Setting this value to ON has the effect of performing an 'I am your manager' action upon the agent.

swLoadInit.name: swLoadInit
swLoadInit.description: Sensors software download procedure initialization message. Includes spe- cific information about the download procedure, such as type of target sen- sor, number of blocks, version.

lntHubAgentSWFault.name: lntHubAgentSWFault
lntHubAgentSWFault.description: Generic fault emitted by agent software. It generally covers all types of faults which cannot be transmitted by the standard types of generic SNMP traps. Uses EnterpriseSpecific traps mechanism.

lntHubAgentEthernetAddr.name: lntHubAgentEthernetAddr
lntHubAgentEthernetAddr.description: Hub agent Ethernet Address - used in previous implementations. Today replaced by interface address in standard MIB II.

lntHubAgentHWVersion.name: lntHubAgentHWVersion
lntHubAgentHWVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the agent hardware version, as known to the agent software.

lntHubAgentSWVersion.name: lntHubAgentSWVersion
lntHubAgentSWVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the agent software version.

lntHubAgentKernelVersion.name: lntHubAgentKernelVersion
lntHubAgentKernelVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the agent operating system (kernel) version.

lntHubAgentFullConfig.name: lntHubAgentFullConfig
lntHubAgentFullConfig.description: Full configuration message sent by agent upon enrollment and at periodic interrogation times. Coded in internal LANNET application format. Up to release 1.5, this attribute was trasmitted to the management console by generic EnterpriseSpecific traps. Starting with release 2.0, it is retrieved by means of Get interogations.

lntHubAgentPerfBusSelection.name: lntHubAgentPerfBusSelection
lntHubAgentPerfBusSelection.description: Attribute describing the bus attached to the performance data collection hardware on those LANNET agent hardware implementations which support configuration management on multi-Ethernet bus enclosures, but performan- ce data collection on a single bus.

lntHubAgentLastAddressConfig.name: lntHubAgentLastAddressConfig
lntHubAgentLastAddressConfig.description: Configuration attribute describing the last physical address detected at each Ethernet port. Coded in internal LANNET application format.

lntHubAgentMgmtBusSelection.name: lntHubAgentMgmtBusSelection
lntHubAgentMgmtBusSelection.description: Attribute describing the bus attached to the performance data collection hardware on those LANNET agent hardware implementations which support configuration management on multi-Ethernet bus enclosures, but performan- ce data collection on a single bus.

lntHubAgentSLIPIpAddress.name: lntHubAgentSLIPIpAddress
lntHubAgentSLIPIpAddress.description: IP address of the SLIP channel of the agent

lntHubAgentHC11CommunicationStatus.name: lntHubAgentHC11CommunicationStatus
lntHubAgentHC11CommunicationStatus.description: Attribute describing the status of the communication with the Master HC11 as detected by the Agent software.

lntHubAgentCommunicationDebugMode.name: lntHubAgentCommunicationDebugMode
lntHubAgentCommunicationDebugMode.description: Attribute describing the agent mode in which communication problem traps are sent to managers (value on) or are not sent to managers (value off).

lntHubHWInternalTemp.name: lntHubHWInternalTemp
lntHubHWInternalTemp.description: Internal enclosure temperature expressed in degrees Celsius.

lntHubHWExternalTemp.name: lntHubHWExternalTemp
lntHubHWExternalTemp.description: External enclosure temperature expressed in degrees Celsius.

lntHubHWInternalPower.name: lntHubHWInternalPower
lntHubHWInternalPower.description: Value EXIST of this attribute signifies existence of an internal power supply on hardware configurations which may contain two (external and internal) power supply units.

lntHubHWExternalPower.name: lntHubHWExternalPower
lntHubHWExternalPower.description: Value EXIST of this attribute signifies existence of an external power sup- ply on hardware configurations which may contain two (external and internal) power supply units.

lntHubHWMainPower.name: lntHubHWMainPower
lntHubHWMainPower.description: This attribute defines the main power supply (internal or external) on hardware configurations represented upon the model of 2 (external and internal) power supply units.

lntHubHWCoolingFan.name: lntHubHWCoolingFan
lntHubHWCoolingFan.description: Value ON of this attribute indicates operation of a cooling fan in the enclosure.

lntHubHWType.name: lntHubHWType
lntHubHWType.description: Indicates type of enclosure in which the LANNET SNMP agent operates.

lntHubHWNumberOfEthernetBuses.name: lntHubHWNumberOfEthernetBuses
lntHubHWNumberOfEthernetBuses.description: Indicates the number of internal Ethernet buses provided by the box.

lntHubHWNumberOfTRBuses.name: lntHubHWNumberOfTRBuses
lntHubHWNumberOfTRBuses.description: Indicates the number of internal Token Ring buses provided by the box.

lntHubHWNumberOfFDDIBuses.name: lntHubHWNumberOfFDDIBuses
lntHubHWNumberOfFDDIBuses.description: Indicates the number of internal FDDI buses provided by the box.

lntGroupHWVersion.name: lntGroupHWVersion
lntGroupHWVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the sensor hardware version, as it is known to the agent software.

lntGroupSWVersion.name: lntGroupSWVersion
lntGroupSWVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the sensor application soft- ware version .

lntGroupKernelVersion.name: lntGroupKernelVersion
lntGroupKernelVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the sensor kernel software version.

lntGroupType.name: lntGroupType
lntGroupType.description: Attribute describing the type of LANNET Ethernet group.

lntGroupFIFO.name: lntGroupFIFO
lntGroupFIFO.description: Value ON of this attribute describes an internal FIFO error sensed by the internal hardware mechanism of a LANNET repeater.

lntGroupJabber.name: lntGroupJabber
lntGroupJabber.description: Value ON of this attribute reflects jabber being transmitted to the bus by the hardware of a LANNET repeater, as a result of collisions detec- ted on the internal bus of the enclosure. Valid for modules LE-10 (all types) and LE-40XT.

lntGroupBusPartition.name: lntGroupBusPartition
lntGroupBusPartition.description: The AutoPart condition indicates that a LANNET repeater is currently par- titioned from the internal bus by the auto-partition mechanism. Valid for all types of LE-10 modules.

lntGroupRedun12.name: lntGroupRedun12
lntGroupRedun12.description: Value ON of this attribute defines a redundancy (backup) relationship between synchronous external ports 1 and 2 on a LANNET module. Valid for modules LE-10B-2, LE-10C-2, LE-20, LE-30X, LE-30X-2, LE-30XD, LE-40X, LE-40XT, LE-80XT, LE-140XT.

lntGroupRedun34.name: lntGroupRedun34
lntGroupRedun34.description: Value ON of this attribute defines a redundancy (backup) relationship between synchronous external ports 3 and 4 on a LANNET module. Valid for modules LE-30X, LE-30XD, LE-40X, LE-40XT.

lntGroup10BTPlus.name: lntGroup10BTPlus
lntGroup10BTPlus.description: Value ON of this attribute defines activation of the 10BaseT+ mode of one of the LE-40XT, LE-80XT, LE-140XT modules. 10BaseT+ is a LANNET exten- sion of the 10BaseT standard.

lntGroupFullConfig.name: lntGroupFullConfig
lntGroupFullConfig.description: Attribute describing the full configuration of a group, in internal LANNET application format.

lntGroupAgentIfType.name: lntGroupAgentIfType
lntGroupAgentIfType.description: This attribute describes the interfaces of agents eventually existing on LANNET modules and their type. Value none defines the lack of an agent or of an interface recognized by the management console. Any other value defines an interface whose type is recognized by the management console and may be used as a management channel.

lntGroupAgentAddress.name: lntGroupAgentAddress
lntGroupAgentAddress.description: This attribute defines an unique address by which the agent may be addres- sed by the management console. The address format should be consistent with the type defined by lntGroupAgentIfType.

lntGroupWrongPortSelection.name: lntGroupWrongPortSelection
lntGroupWrongPortSelection.description: A value ON of this attribute warns of incorrect selection of enabled ports on sensors which impose restrictions on this configura- tion (e.g. integrated local bridges.

lntGroupSupplyVoltageFault.name: lntGroupSupplyVoltageFault
lntGroupSupplyVoltageFault.description: A value ON of this attribute informs of a 'voltage supply out-of-range' error candition on sensor hardware which checks this condition.

lntGroupNumberOfIntPorts.name: lntGroupNumberOfIntPorts
lntGroupNumberOfIntPorts.description: Number of internal ports (ports connected to the enclosure buses) on the sensor.

lntGroupInPortsRedundancy.name: lntGroupInPortsRedundancy
lntGroupInPortsRedundancy.description: Value ON of this attribute defines a redundancy (backup) relationship between internal ports 1 and 2 on a LANNET module.

lntGroupStandAloneModeSwitch.name: lntGroupStandAloneModeSwitch
lntGroupStandAloneModeSwitch.description: Value ON of this attribute indicates the sensor's operation Stand Alone mode . Internal ports are disabled and the card functions in a local star configuration toward its external ports.

lntGroupId.name: lntGroupId
lntGroupId.description: Unique ID number for the group in the lntGroupTable.

lntGroupDescr.name: lntGroupDescr
lntGroupDescr.description: Descriptor of the group in ASCII (readable) format, mainly for use with generic management applications.

lntGroupBackboneMode.name: lntGroupBackboneMode
lntGroupBackboneMode.description: Value On of this attribute defines Backbone Mode of a sensor. Internal ports are enabled and the information path goes straightly from external port to internal bus, via corresponding internal port.

lntGroupFOIRLPlusMode.name: lntGroupFOIRLPlusMode
lntGroupFOIRLPlusMode.description: Value On of this attribute defines FOIRL of a sensor. When this attribute has value ON, FOIRL Plus mode is enabled, while value OFF indicates stan- dard FOIRL mode.

lntGroupLATStatus.name: lntGroupLATStatus
lntGroupLATStatus.description: Value ON of this attribute means that LAT protocol is Enabled on the LANNET Ethernet module.

lntGroupInterProcCommStatus.name: lntGroupInterProcCommStatus
lntGroupInterProcCommStatus.description: This attribute describes the status of the communication between the microprocessor of the sensor and the microprocessor of the agent on cards with embedded agents.

lntGroupOperationMode.name: lntGroupOperationMode
lntGroupOperationMode.description: This attribute describes the operation mode of the module in a multiprocessor configuration sensor, as reported by interprocessors communication.

lntGroupCommunicationStatus.name: lntGroupCommunicationStatus
lntGroupCommunicationStatus.description: This attribute describes the communication status of the group with the SNMP Agent as detected and reported by the agent.

lntGroupHardwareStatus.name: lntGroupHardwareStatus
lntGroupHardwareStatus.description: This attribute describes the status of the group hardware as detected by the sensors software.

lntPortType.name: lntPortType
lntPortType.description: Attribute describing the type of LANNET port.

lntPortJabber.name: lntPortJabber
lntPortJabber.description: Value ON of this attribute reflects jabber transmitted to the port by the hardware of a LANNET repeater or transceiver, as a result of collisions detected on the port. Valid for all modules in the LE-10 and LE-15 families.

lntPortNoAUILoop.name: lntPortNoAUILoop
lntPortNoAUILoop.description: Value ON of this attribute indicates that a No AUI Loop fault condition was detected on an AUI repeater port. Valid for LE-10C family of modu- les.

lntPortFunctionalStatus.name: lntPortFunctionalStatus
lntPortFunctionalStatus.description: The value of this attribute reflects the functional status of LANNET synchronous ports. Note that it is not mandatory that all ports support all the enumerated states. Here is the minimal set possible states: OK - fully functional port, transmitting and receiving packets. RLD - receive link down condition on the port. TLD - transmit link down condition on the port. LocalJabber - fault condition indicating that the port emitted jabber. RemoteJabber - fault condition indicating that remote jabber was sensed at the port. IllSeq - Fault condition indicating an illegal synchronization sequence at the port. ShortCircuit - short-circuit fault condition detected at the port.

lntPortManPart.name: lntPortManPart
lntPortManPart.description: Setting to the value of this attribute to ON activates the manual partition mechanism at the port level. Setting the value of this attribute to OFF cancels the partition sechanism. The segment may reconnect after the reception of 32 packets. Attribute vaild for repeater modules from the LE-10 family.

lntPortActivityStatus.name: lntPortActivityStatus
lntPortActivityStatus.description: This attribute defines the status of ports that may be part of a redundan- cy scheme. NotActive - indicates a disabled port which cannot transmit or receive pac- kets even if included in a redundancy scheme. Dormant - indicates an enabled port which does not transmit or receive pac- kets, but because it is included in a redundancy scheme, it may at any moment become responsible packet transmission and reception. Active - indicates that the port transmits and receives packets, serving as the main path in the redundant configuration.

lntPortGroupId.name: lntPortGroupId
lntPortGroupId.description: Id of the group to which the port belongs.

lntPortId.name: lntPortId
lntPortId.description: Unique Id of the port in the lntPortTable.

lntPortDescr.name: lntPortDescr
lntPortDescr.description: Descriptor of the port in ASCII (readable) format, mainly for use with generic management applications.

lntPortIntPortConnection.name: lntPortIntPortConnection
lntPortIntPortConnection.description: The value of this attribute defines the internal port to which the port is connected.

lntIntPortGroupId.name: lntIntPortGroupId
lntIntPortGroupId.description: ID of the group to which the internal port belongs.

lntIntPortId.name: lntIntPortId
lntIntPortId.description: ID of the internal port in the lntPortTable.

lntIntPortAdminStatus.name: lntIntPortAdminStatus
lntIntPortAdminStatus.description: A disabled internal port neither transmits or receives. The port must be explicitly enabled to restore operation.

lntIntPortActivityStatus.name: lntIntPortActivityStatus
lntIntPortActivityStatus.description: This attribute defines the status of internal ports that may be part of a redundancy scheme. NotActive - indicates a disabled port which cannot transmit or receive pac- kets even if included in a redundancy scheme. Dormant - indicates an enabled port which does not transmit or receive pac- kets, but because it is included in a redundancy scheme, it may at any moment become responsible for packet transmission and reception. Active - indicates that the port transmits and receives packets, serving as the main path in the redundant configuration.

lntIntPortPartition.name: lntIntPortPartition
lntIntPortPartition.description: This condition indicates that the internal port is currently partitioned from the bus by the auto-partition protection mechanism.

lntIntPortBusConnection.name: lntIntPortBusConnection
lntIntPortBusConnection.description: The value of this attribute defines the bus to which the internal port is connected. Internal Ethernet buses are numbered 1 and 2 in LET-18 enclosures and 1 to 4 in LET-36 enclosures.

trGroupID.name: trGroupID
trGroupID.description: Unique ID of the group in trGroupTable. Equivalent to slot number in LANNET enclosures.

trGroupNumberOfPorts.name: trGroupNumberOfPorts
trGroupNumberOfPorts.description: Number of ports in group. Range 1..255. It is assumed that on each group the ports are assigned unique numbers in the range from 1 to TRGroupNumberOfPorts. They correspond to the number of ports on the module (FRU)

trGroupAutoMan.name: trGroupAutoMan
trGroupAutoMan.description: This attribute reflects the status of the Auto/Manual switch which defines the working mode of LANNET sensors. In the MANUAL mode no set operations may be performed on attributes related to the sensor. The sensor works according to configuration switches set by hardware and transmits all configuration information to the agent. In the AUTO mode, hardware switches are overridden by set commands.

trGroupReset.name: trGroupReset
trGroupReset.description: Setting the value of this attribute to ON is interpreted as a software RESET command. Sensor software is reinitialised and acording to the sensor specifications, partial or total reset of the module hardware may be performed.

trGroupHWVersion.name: trGroupHWVersion
trGroupHWVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the sensor hardware version, as it is known to the agent software.

trGroupSWVersion.name: trGroupSWVersion
trGroupSWVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the sensor application soft- ware version.

trGroupKernelVersion.name: trGroupKernelVersion
trGroupKernelVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the sensor kernel software version.

trGroupType.name: trGroupType
trGroupType.description: Attribute describing the type of LANNET token ring group.

trGroupFullConfig.name: trGroupFullConfig
trGroupFullConfig.description: Attribute describing the full configuration of a token ring group in in- ternal LANNET application format.

trGroupAutoRightLoop.name: trGroupAutoRightLoop
trGroupAutoRightLoop.description: Value ON of this attribute signifies that a hardware loop was automatically created on a Token Ring module which does not sense the existence of another token ring group on the right hand side.

trGroupAutoLeftLoop.name: trGroupAutoLeftLoop
trGroupAutoLeftLoop.description: Value ON of this attribute signifies that a hardware loop was automatically created on a Token Ring module which does not sense the existence of another token ring group on the left hand side.

trGroupManRightloop.name: trGroupManRightloop
trGroupManRightloop.description: Setting this attribute to ON signifies a command to the hardware to create a loop on the Token Ring module which isolates the ring from the right hand side.

trGroupManLeftLoop.name: trGroupManLeftLoop
trGroupManLeftLoop.description: Setting this attribute to ON signifies a command to the hardware to create a loop on the Token Ring module which isolates the ring from the left hand side.

trGroupRightNeigbour.name: trGroupRightNeigbour
trGroupRightNeigbour.description: Attribute defining the existence of a neighbor another token ring group on the right hand side of the module.

trGroupLeftNeigbour.name: trGroupLeftNeigbour
trGroupLeftNeigbour.description: Attribute defining the existence of a neighbor another token ring group on the left hand side of the module.

trGroupIoMode.name: trGroupIoMode
trGroupIoMode.description: Attribute defining the I/O mode (single, dual-ring-in, dual-ring-out) Lobe, Internal Repeater or Star) of a module from the the LTR-IO family.

trGroupRingSpeed.name: trGroupRingSpeed
trGroupRingSpeed.description: Attribute describing the bandwidth of the ring. In case of bridges it describes the speed of the first ring.

trGroupTxLinkDown.name: trGroupTxLinkDown
trGroupTxLinkDown.description: Value ON of this attribute defines a TxLinkDown fault condition on a LANNET Token Ring repeater module.

trGroupRxLinkDown.name: trGroupRxLinkDown
trGroupRxLinkDown.description: Value ON of this attribute defines an RxLinkDown fault condition on a LANNET Token Ring repeater module.

trGroupManLinkLoop.name: trGroupManLinkLoop
trGroupManLinkLoop.description: Setting the value of this attribute to ON instructs the hardware of a LANNET Token Ring repeater module to close the loop in the direction of the external connection.

trGroupManBusLoop.name: trGroupManBusLoop
trGroupManBusLoop.description: Setting the value of this attribute to ON instructs the hardware of a LANNET Token Ring repeater module to close the loop in the direction of the internal bus.

trGroupAutoLinkLoop.name: trGroupAutoLinkLoop
trGroupAutoLinkLoop.description: Value ON of this attribute signifies that a hardware loop has been auto- matically closed by the hardwar of the LANNET Token Ring repeater as a result of problems on the external link.

trGroupAutoBusLoop.name: trGroupAutoBusLoop
trGroupAutoBusLoop.description: Value ON of this attribute signifies that a hardware loop has been auto- matically closed by the hardware of the LANNET Token Ring repeater as a result of problems on the internal bus.

trGroupIOModeF.name: trGroupIOModeF
trGroupIOModeF.description: Attribute defining the I/O mode (Ring-in, Ring-out) of a LANNET Token Ring repeater.

trGroupDescr.name: trGroupDescr
trGroupDescr.description: Descriptor of the group in ASCII (readable) format, mainly for use with generic management applications.

trGroupAgentIfType.name: trGroupAgentIfType
trGroupAgentIfType.description: This attribute describes the interfaces of agents eventually existing on LANNET modules and their type. Value none defines the lack of agent or of an interface recognized by the management console, while any other value defines an interface whose type is recognized by the the management console and may be used as a management channel.

trGroupAgentAddress.name: trGroupAgentAddress
trGroupAgentAddress.description: This attribute defines an unique address by which the agent may be addres- sed by the management console. The address format should be consistent with the type defined by trGroupAgentIfType.

trGroupSecondRingSpeed.name: trGroupSecondRingSpeed
trGroupSecondRingSpeed.description: Attribute describing bandwidth of the ring. In case of bridges it describes the speed of the second ring.

trGroupBridgeMode.name: trGroupBridgeMode
trGroupBridgeMode.description: Attribute describing the operational mode of the bridge. For ITLB the following modes are defined: - Mode A: First channel connected to an external ring (RI,RO connectors) and second channel connected to an internal ring; - Mode B: First channel connected to an external ring by a DTE connector and second channel connected to an internal ring; - Mode C: First channel connected to an internal left ring and second channel connected to an internal right ring.

trGroupFirstRingInserted.name: trGroupFirstRingInserted
trGroupFirstRingInserted.description: Attribute describing that the first ring in the case of a bridge requires or not insertion.

trGroupSecondRingInserted.name: trGroupSecondRingInserted
trGroupSecondRingInserted.description: Attribute describing that the second ring in the case of a bridge requires or not insertion.

trGroupStandAloneModeSwitch.name: trGroupStandAloneModeSwitch
trGroupStandAloneModeSwitch.description: Value On of this attribute defines Stand Alone Mode of a sensor. Internal ports are disabled and the card functions in a local star configuration to- ward its external ports.

trGroupRedun12.name: trGroupRedun12
trGroupRedun12.description: Value ON of this attribute defines a redundancy (back-up) relation between synchronous external ports 1 and 2 on a LANNET module.

trGroupRedun34.name: trGroupRedun34
trGroupRedun34.description: Value ON of this attribute defines a redundancy (back-up) relation between synchronous external ports 3 and 4 on a LANNET module.

trGroupSuperRedundancy.name: trGroupSuperRedundancy
trGroupSuperRedundancy.description: Value ON of this attribute defines a redundancy (back-up) relation between all the internal ports on a LANNET module. By default port 1 is active, backed by port 2, backed by port 3 (if existing), etc.

trGroupInterProcCommStatus.name: trGroupInterProcCommStatus
trGroupInterProcCommStatus.description: This attribute describes the status of the communication between the microprocessor of the sensor and the microprocessor of the agent on cards with embedded agents.

trGroupCommunicationStatus.name: trGroupCommunicationStatus
trGroupCommunicationStatus.description: This attribute describes the communication status of the group with the SNMP Agent as detected and reported by the agent.

trGroupHardwareStatus.name: trGroupHardwareStatus
trGroupHardwareStatus.description: This attribute describes the status of the group hardware as detected by the sensors software.

trPortType.name: trPortType
trPortType.description: Attribute describing the type of Token Ring LANNET port.

trPortID.name: trPortID
trPortID.description: Unique ID of the port in the trPortTable.

trPortBypass.name: trPortBypass
trPortBypass.description: Setting the value of this attribute to ON causes the by- passing of the TokenRing LANNET port.

trPortConnected.name: trPortConnected
trPortConnected.description: Attribute which describes the connection status of a Token Ring port (in- clusion of the Token Ring controller in the ring).

trPortTcp.name: trPortTcp
trPortTcp.description: Setting the value of this attribute to ON causes the activation of the cable-fault detection mechanism.

trPortCableFault.name: trPortCableFault
trPortCableFault.description: Value ON of this attribute signifies the detection of a cable-fault on this specific Token Ring port.

trPortGroupID.name: trPortGroupID
trPortGroupID.description: ID of group to which the Token Ring port belongs.

trPortDescr.name: trPortDescr
trPortDescr.description: Descriptor of the group in ASCII (readable) format, mainly for use with generic management applications.

trPortFunctionalStatus.name: trPortFunctionalStatus
trPortFunctionalStatus.description: The value of this attribute reflects the functional status of LANNET Token Ring ports. Note that it is not mandatory that a certain port support all the enumerated states. Here is the lest of the possible states: OK - fully functional port, transmitting and receiving packets. RLD - receive link down condition on the port. TLD - transmit link down condition on the port.

trPortActivityStatus.name: trPortActivityStatus
trPortActivityStatus.description: This attribute defines the status of ports who may be part of a redundan- cy schema. NotActive indicates a disabled port which cannot transmit or receive pac- kets even if included in a redundancy scheme. Dormant indicates an enabled port which does not transmit or receive pac- kets, but included in a redundancy schema is at any moment disponible for packets transmission and reception. Active indicates that the port transmits and receives packets, as the main path in the redundant configuration.

trIntPortGroupId.name: trIntPortGroupId
trIntPortGroupId.description: Id of the group to which the internal port belongs.

trIntPortId.name: trIntPortId
trIntPortId.description: Id of the internal port in the trInPortTable.

trIntPortBusConnection.name: trIntPortBusConnection
trIntPortBusConnection.description: The value of this attribute defines the bus to which the internal port is connected. Internal Ethernet buses are numbered 1,2 in LET18 enclosures and 1 to 4 in LET36 enclosures.

trIntPortAdminStatus.name: trIntPortAdminStatus
trIntPortAdminStatus.description: A disabled port neither transmits or receives. The port must be explicitely enabled to restore operation.

trRingIndex.name: trRingIndex
trRingIndex.description: Id of the ring in the trRingTable.

trRingCurTraffic.name: trRingCurTraffic
trRingCurTraffic.description: Record of traffic for the last second with a resolution of 100 msec. The traffic is expressed in percents of the maximum effective TR traffic (token messages are excluded) and each record contains 10 readings, in range 1..20 on log(10) scale.

trRingTrafficTrsh.name: trRingTrafficTrsh
trRingTrafficTrsh.description: Traffic threshold value. When exceeded, a trap is send to the management console. Expressed in percents of the maximum effective TR traffic (token messages are excluded) in the range 1..20 on log(10) scale.

trRingPeakTraffic.name: trRingPeakTraffic
trRingPeakTraffic.description: Maximal traffic value since last reset of agent. Expressed in percents of the maximum effective TR traffic (token messages are excluded), in the range 1..20 on log(10) scale.

srlportGroupID.name: srlportGroupID
srlportGroupID.description: ID of group to which the Terminal Server port belongs.

srlportID.name: srlportID
srlportID.description: Unique Id of the port in the srlportEntry.

srlportType.name: srlportType
srlportType.description: Attribute describing the type of the LANNET Terminal Server port.

srlportAdminStatus.name: srlportAdminStatus
srlportAdminStatus.description: A disabled port neither transmits or receives. The port must be explicitely enabled to restore operation.

srlportDescr.name: srlportDescr
srlportDescr.description: Descriptor of the group in ASCII (readable) format, mainly for use with generic management applications.

ltGroupID.name: ltGroupID
ltGroupID.description: Unique ID of the group in ltGroupTable. Equivalent to slot number in LANNET enclosures.

ltGroupNumberOfPorts.name: ltGroupNumberOfPorts
ltGroupNumberOfPorts.description: Number of ports in group. Range 1..255. It is assumed that on each group the ports are numbered uniquely in the range from 1 to standardGroupNumberOf Ports. They corespond to the number of ports of the module (FRU)

ltGroupAutoMan.name: ltGroupAutoMan
ltGroupAutoMan.description: This attribute reflects the status of the auto/manual switch which defi- nes the working mode of LANNET sensors. On Manual mode no set operations may be performed on attributes related to sensor. The sensor works acor- ding to configuration switches set by hardware methods and transmits all configuration information to the agent. On Auto mode hardware switches are overridden by set commands.

ltGroupReset.name: ltGroupReset
ltGroupReset.description: Setting the value of this attribute to ON is interpreted as a software RESET command. Sensor software is reinitialised and acording to the sensor specifications, partial or total reset of the module hardware may be performed.

ltGroupHWVersion.name: ltGroupHWVersion
ltGroupHWVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the sensor hardware version, as it is known by the agent software.

ltGroupSWVersion.name: ltGroupSWVersion
ltGroupSWVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the sensor application soft- ware.

ltGroupKernelVersion.name: ltGroupKernelVersion
ltGroupKernelVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the sensor kernel software.

ltGroupType.name: ltGroupType
ltGroupType.description: Attribute describing the type of LANNET Terminal Server group.

ltGroupFullConfig.name: ltGroupFullConfig
ltGroupFullConfig.description: Attribute describing the full configuration of a terminal server group in internal LANNET application format.

ltGroupDescr.name: ltGroupDescr
ltGroupDescr.description: Descriptor of the group in ASCII (readable) format, mainly for use with generic management applications.

ltGroupInterProcCommStatus.name: ltGroupInterProcCommStatus
ltGroupInterProcCommStatus.description: This attribute describes the status of the communication between the microprocessor of the sensor and the microprocessor of the agent on cards with embedded agents.

ltGroupStandAloneModeSwitch.name: ltGroupStandAloneModeSwitch
ltGroupStandAloneModeSwitch.description: Value On of this attribute defines Stand Alone Mode of a sensor. Internal ports are disabled and the card functions in a local star configuration to- ward its external ports.

ltGroupCommunicationStatus.name: ltGroupCommunicationStatus
ltGroupCommunicationStatus.description: This attribute describes the communication status of the group with the SNMP Agent as detected and reported by the agent.

ltPortGroupID.name: ltPortGroupID
ltPortGroupID.description: ID of group to which the Local Talk card belongs.

ltPortID.name: ltPortID
ltPortID.description: Unique Id of the port in the ltPortEntry.

ltPortType.name: ltPortType
ltPortType.description: Attribute describing the type of the LANNET Local Talk card port.

ltPortAdminStatus.name: ltPortAdminStatus
ltPortAdminStatus.description: A disabled port neither transmits or receives. The port must be explicitely enabled to restore operation.

ltPortTest.name: ltPortTest
ltPortTest.description: A value ON of this attribute indicates that a port test should be performed upon the port defined be the attribute instance.

ltPortTestResult.name: ltPortTestResult
ltPortTestResult.description: Indicates the result of a port test performed on this port.

ltPortJam.name: ltPortJam
ltPortJam.description: An ON value of this attribute indicates a Jam error on the specific port.

ltPortDescr.name: ltPortDescr
ltPortDescr.description: Descriptor of the group in ASCII (readable) format, mainly for use with generic management applications.

ltIntPortGroupId.name: ltIntPortGroupId
ltIntPortGroupId.description: Id of the group to which the internal port belongs.

ltIntPortId.name: ltIntPortId
ltIntPortId.description: Id of the internal port in the ltIntPortTable.

ltIntPortAdminStatus.name: ltIntPortAdminStatus
ltIntPortAdminStatus.description: A disabled internal port neither transmits or receives. The port must be explicitely enabled to restore operation.

ltIntPortBusConnection.name: ltIntPortBusConnection
ltIntPortBusConnection.description: The value of this attribute defines the bus to which the internal port is connected. Local Talk cards inserted in LET18 type enclosures may access 2 buses, while Local Talk cards inserted in LET18 type enclosures may access 4 buses.
